        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 6:24PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 624 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles north of Matheson, or 16 miles west of Limon, moving east at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Matheson and Cedar Point.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rain is occurring with this storm and may lead to flooding. Do
not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
